The paper focuses on measuring engagement in a Human-Robot Interaction (HRI) setting, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed model utilizes convolutional neural networks (CNN) and long short-term memory (LSTM) networks to analyze video streams, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The goal of the model is to improve metrics of interaction quality and guide interaction design, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the transferability of the model to different datasets, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG).
